Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I think there's promise here, but something that made this work for the build page was that the three columns had some semantic grouping.  There's at least some idea that when looking at a column that you will find related information in proximity.  The job page is sort of a grab bag of information; finding a grouping that works may be more difficult.

At any rate, without that grouping, and with the irregular vertical spacing here, this is harder to scan than the plain vertical layout.  If those two things can be addressed, I think this would be an improvement.

Patch Set 1:

> At any rate, without that grouping, and with the irregular vertical spacing here, this is harder to scan than the plain vertical layout.  If those two things can be addressed, I think this would be an improvement.

Upon looking at this again; I think that removing the horizontal formatting (so descriptions go above values, not next to) and restricting this to two columns, instead of 3, makes this look much clearer.  Another improvement is I09c4174379dde38e3f55cb731bc991039c4a4dd2 which reduces the header bringing more of the page into view.

Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

(2 comments)

Thanks for taking this on.

I think as long as you're doing this, you should also follow nova in adding the non_inheritable_image_properties config option and associated stuff (there's also a hardcoded list of NON_INHERITABLE_IMAGE_PROPERTIES in nova), because there are other image properties that can cause similar problems (probably the same list of properties nova has).  We need the config option (not just the hard-coded list) because glance property protections leave the possibility that an operator has configured read-only image properties in glance, and if so, they can use the option in cinder so that cinder doesn't try to write them when creating an image in glance.
